(70, 32, 'Lung Cancer ', 'Lung cancer is a type of cancer that begins in the cells of the lungs. It is the leading cause of cancer-related deaths worldwide. \r\nThere are two main types of lung cancer: non-small cell lung cancer (NSCLC) and small cell lung cancer (SCLC). NSCLC is the most common type, accounting for about 80% of all lung cancer cases. SCLC is less common, but it tends to grow and spread more quickly than NSCLC. \r\nThe most common cause of lung cancer is smoking, including both active and passive smoking. Other risk factors for lung cancer include exposure to radon, asbestos, and other harmful chemicals, as well as a family history of lung cancer. ', 'Persistent cough \r\nChest pain \r\nShortness of breath \r\nHoarseness \r\nWeight loss \r\nFatigue ', 'Treatment for lung cancer may include surgery, radiation therapy, chemotherapy, targeted therapy, or immunotherapy, depending on the type and stage of the disease. The choice of treatment depends on several factors, including the type and stage of the cancer, the person\'s overall health, and the presence of any other medical conditions. \r\nPrevention measures for lung cancer include not smoking or quitting smoking, avoiding exposure to secondhand smoke, testing homes for radon, and limiting exposure to other harmful chemicals. Early diagnosis and treatment are important for improving outcomes and increasing the chances of a cure. ', NULL, '2023-05-23 08:03:58'),
(71, 32, 'Malaria ', 'Malaria is a serious and potentially life-threatening infectious disease that is caused by a type of parasite called Plasmodium. It is transmitted to humans through the bites of infected female Anopheles mosquitoes, which carry the parasite in their saliva. \r\nMalaria is most commonly found in tropical and subtropical regions of the world, particularly in sub-Saharan Africa, South Asia, and parts of Central and South America. ', 'Fever \r\nHeadache \r\nMuscle \r\nPain \r\nFatigue ', 'Treatment for malaria typically involves a combination of medications that target the parasite at different stages of its life cycle. However, if left untreated, malaria can lead to severe complications such as organ failure, seizures, and coma, and can even be fatal. \r\nThe disease can be prevented through the use of insecticide-treated bed nets, indoor residual spraying, and the administration of antimalarial drugs. ', NULL, '2023-05-23 08:04:39'),
(72, 32, 'Malignant Brain Tumour ', 'A malignant brain tumor is a type of cancerous tumor that originates in the cells of the brain or spinal cord. It is characterized by the abnormal growth of cells that do not die as they normally would and can continue to divide and spread uncontrollably throughout the brain. \r\nMalignant brain tumors can be primary or secondary. Primary brain tumors originate in the brain itself, while secondary brain tumors (also known as metastatic brain tumors) are cancerous cells that have spread from another part of the body, such as the lungs, breast, or skin. ', 'Headaches \r\nSeizures \r\nChanges in vision or speech \r\nDifficulty with balance or coordination \r\nCognitive or personality changes ', 'Treatment for malignant brain tumors may involve a combination of surgery, radiation therapy, and chemotherapy. The goals of treatment are to remove as much of the tumor as possible, slow down or stop its growth, and relieve symptoms. However, prognosis can vary depending on factors such as the type, location, and size of the tumor, as well as the age and overall health of the patient. ', NULL, '2023-05-23 08:05:29'),
(73, 32, 'Marburg Virus Hemorrhagic Fever ', 'Marburg virus hemorrhagic fever is a rare but highly infectious and severe viral disease that is characterized by fever, headache, muscle pain, and hemorrhagic (bleeding) symptoms. The disease is caused by the Marburg virus, a member of the Filoviridae family, which is related to the Ebola virus. \r\nMarburg virus is primarily transmitted to humans through direct contact with the bodily fluids (such as blood, saliva, or vomit) of infected animals, such as monkeys and bats, or through contact with the bodily fluids of infected humans. Once a person is infected, the virus rapidly multiplies in the body and can cause damage to multiple organs, leading to severe illness and death. ', 'Fever \r\nHeadache \r\nMuscle pain \r\nWeakness \r\nVomiting \r\nDiarrhea \r\nAbdominal pain \r\nBleeding from various parts of the body ', 'There is currently no specific treatment or vaccine for Marburg virus hemorrhagic fever, and management typically involves supportive care, including intravenous fluids, electrolyte replacement, and treatment of complications. Prevention measures include avoiding contact with infected animals and people, practicing good hand hygiene, and wearing protective clothing when working with infected individuals or animals. ', NULL, '2023-05-23 08:06:27'),
(74, 32, 'Melioidosis ', 'Melioidosis, also known as Whitmore\'s disease, is a rare and potentially fatal infectious disease caused by the bacterium Burkholderia pseudomallei. It is most commonly found in tropical regions of Southeast Asia and Northern Australia, but has been reported in other parts of the world as well. \r\nMelioidosis can be contracted through contact with contaminated soil or water, or through inhalation of the bacteria. The disease can affect multiple organs and systems in the body, including the lungs, liver, spleen, kidneys, and brain. ', 'Pneumonia\r\nSepsis\r\nAbscesses', 'Melioidosis can be difficult to diagnose, as the symptoms can mimic other diseases such as tuberculosis and pneumonia. Diagnosis typically involves laboratory testing of blood, urine, or other bodily fluids to detect the presence of the bacteria. \r\nTreatment for melioidosis involves antibiotics, often for an extended period of time, and supportive care for any complications that may arise. Prevention measures include avoiding exposure to contaminated soil and water, wearing protective clothing and footwear when working in high-risk areas, and practicing good hygiene. ', NULL, '2023-05-23 08:08:07'),
(75, 32, 'Measles ', 'Measles, also known as rubeola, is a highly contagious viral disease that is caused by the measles virus. It is spread through airborne droplets when an infected person coughs or sneezes. The disease is characterized by a fever, cough, runny nose, and a rash that spreads all over the body. ', 'High fever\r\nRunny nose\r\nCough\r\nRed and watery eyes\r\nSmall white spots inside the cheeks ', 'There is no specific treatment for measles, and management typically involves supportive care to relieve symptoms, such as fever and cough. However, vaccination is highly effective at preventing measles. The measles vaccine is typically administered as part of the measles-mumps-rubella (MMR) vaccine, which is recommended for all children at age 12-15 months, with a second dose at age 4-6 years. Adults who have not been vaccinated or have not had measles in the past should also receive the vaccine. \r\nGlobal efforts to increase measles vaccination coverage have resulted in a significant decrease in the number of cases worldwide, but outbreaks still occur in areas with low vaccination rates. ', NULL, '2023-05-23 08:11:18'),
(76, 25, 'Meningococcal disease ', 'Meningococcal disease is a serious bacterial infection caused by the bacteria Neisseria meningitidis. It can cause meningitis, an inflammation of the membranes that cover the brain and spinal cord, as well as septicemia, a severe bloodstream infection. \r\nMeningococcal disease is spread through respiratory or throat secretions, such as saliva or mucus, and can be transmitted through close contact with an infected person, such as coughing, sneezing, or kissing. It is most common in infants, young children, adolescents, and young adults. ', 'Fever \r\nHeadache \r\nStiff neck \r\nSensitivity to light \r\nConfusion \r\nNausea \r\nVomiting \r\nA characteristic rash that does not fade when pressed ', 'Treatment for meningococcal disease typically involves hospitalization and administration of antibiotics, as well as supportive care for any complications that may arise. Prevention measures include vaccination against the most common strains of the bacteria, practicing good hygiene, and avoiding close contact with people who are sick. \r\nVaccination is highly effective at preventing meningococcal disease, and is recommended for all children at age 11-12 years, with a booster dose at age 16 years. Other high-risk groups, such as college students and travelers to areas with high rates of the disease, may also benefit from vaccination. ', NULL, '2023-05-23 08:13:25'),
(77, 25, 'Naegleria Fowleri ', 'Naegleria fowleri is a microscopic amoeba (single-celled organism) that can cause a rare and severe brain infection called primary amebic meningoencephalitis (PAM). The amoeba is found in warm freshwater and soil, and enters the body through the nose when people swim or dive in warm freshwater or when they use contaminated tap water for nasal irrigation. ', 'Fever \r\nHeadache \r\nNausea \r\nVomiting \r\nStiff neck \r\nSeizures \r\nConfusion \r\nComa ', 'Although Naegleria fowleri infections are rare, they are often fatal, making it important to take preventive measures when swimming or diving in warm freshwater or using tap water for nasal irrigation. Prevention measures include avoiding swimming or diving in warm freshwater during periods of high water temperature, keeping the head above water, using nose clips, and avoiding nasal irrigation with untreated tap water. \r\nThere is no specific treatment for Naegleria fowleri infection, and management involves supportive care to relieve symptoms. Early diagnosis and treatment may improve the chances of survival, but the infection is usually fatal. ', NULL, '2023-05-23 08:14:39'),
(78, 25, 'Norovirus Infection ', 'Norovirus infection is a highly contagious viral illness that can cause gastroenteritis, which is inflammation of the stomach and intestines. The virus is transmitted through contaminated food or water, contact with contaminated surfaces, or direct contact with an infected person. ', 'Nausea \r\nVomiting \r\nDiarrhea \r\nStomach cramps \r\nFever \r\nBody aches ', 'Treatment for norovirus infection involves supportive care to relieve symptoms and prevent dehydration, such as drinking fluids to replace lost fluids and electrolytes. There is no specific antiviral medication for norovirus infection. \r\nPrevention measures include practicing good hygiene, such as washing hands frequently with soap and water, disinfecting contaminated surfaces, and avoiding contact with infected individuals or their bodily fluids. It is also important to properly prepare and handle food to avoid contamination. \r\nNorovirus infection is common in places such as hospitals, schools, and cruise ships, where large groups of people are in close contact. Outbreaks of the virus can occur at any time of year, but are more common in the winter months. ', NULL, '2023-05-23 08:15:51'),
(79, 25, 'Norwalk Virus', 'Norwalk virus is a type of norovirus, which is a highly contagious viral illness that can cause gastroenteritis. The virus is transmitted through contaminated food or water, contact with contaminated surfaces, or direct contact with an infected person. \r\nThe Norwalk virus was named after the Norwalk outbreak of gastroenteritis that occurred in 1968 in Norwalk, Ohio, United States. The virus is now known to be one of the most common causes of gastroenteritis worldwide, causing outbreaks in a variety of settings including schools, nursing homes, and cruise ships. ', 'Nausea \r\nVomiting \r\nDiarrhea \r\nStomach cramps \r\nFever \r\nBody aches ', 'Treatment for norovirus infection involves supportive care to relieve symptoms and prevent dehydration, such as drinking fluids to replace lost fluids and electrolytes. There is no specific antiviral medication for norovirus infection. \r\nPrevention measures for Norwalk virus and norovirus infections include practicing good hygiene, such as washing hands frequently with soap and water, disinfecting contaminated surfaces, and avoiding contact with infected individuals or their bodily fluids. It is also important to properly prepare and handle food to avoid contamination. ', NULL, '2023-05-23 08:17:01'),
(80, 25, 'Non-Gonococcal Urethritis    ', 'Non-gonococcal urethritis (NGU) is a sexually transmitted infection (STI) that affects the urethra, which is the tube that carries urine from the bladder out of the body. NGU is caused by bacteria other than Neisseria gonorrhoeae, which causes gonorrhea. ', 'Pain or discomfort when urinating \r\nDischarge from the penis \r\nItching or irritation in the urethra ', 'Diagnosis of NGU may involve a physical exam, as well as urine and/or swab samples to test for the presence of bacteria. Antibiotic treatment is often used to treat NGU, and sexual partners may also need to be treated to prevent reinfection. \r\nPrevention measures for NGU and other STIs include practicing safe sex (such as using condoms or dental dams), getting tested regularly for STIs, and avoiding sexual contact with anyone who has symptoms of an STI. It is also important to have open and honest communication with sexual partners about sexual health and history. ', NULL, '2023-05-23 08:17:37'),
(81, 25, 'Oral Cancer ', 'Oral cancer refers to cancer that develops in the tissues of the mouth or throat. The majority of oral cancers are squamous cell carcinomas, which are cancers that develop in the thin, flat cells that line the mouth and throat. \r\nThe most common risk factors for oral cancer include tobacco use (including cigarettes, cigars, and smokeless tobacco), heavy alcohol consumption, and infection with the human papillomavirus (HPV). Other risk factors may include a history of head and neck cancer, exposure to certain chemicals or irritants, and poor oral hygiene. ', 'A sore or lump in the mouth that doesn\'t heal \r\nPain or difficulty swallowing \r\nA persistent sore throat \r\nA change in voice \r\nA white or red patch on the gums, tongue, or lining of the mouth ', 'Treatment for oral cancer depends on the stage and location of the cancer, and may involve surgery, radiation therapy, chemotherapy, or a combination of these treatments. In some cases, targeted therapy or immunotherapy may also be used. \r\nPrevention measures for oral cancer include avoiding tobacco use, limiting alcohol consumption, practicing good oral hygiene, and getting the HPV vaccine. Regular dental checkups are also important for early detection and treatment of oral cancer. ', NULL, '2023-05-23 08:18:32'),
(82, 25, 'Ovarian Cancer ', 'Ovarian cancer is a type of cancer that develops in the ovaries, which are the female reproductive organs that produce eggs. Ovarian cancer is often called the \"silent killer\" because it can develop without causing any symptoms in its early stages. \r\nThe exact cause of ovarian cancer is not known, but certain risk factors may increase a woman\'s likelihood of developing the disease. These risk factors may include a family history of ovarian or breast cancer, age (most ovarian cancers occur in women over the age of 50), infertility, hormone therapy, and certain genetic mutations. ', 'Bloating \r\nAbdominal or pelvic pain \r\nDifficulty eating or feeling full quickly \r\nFrequent urination \r\nChanges in bowel habit ', 'Diagnosis of ovarian cancer may involve a physical exam, imaging tests (such as ultrasound or CT scan), and blood tests to check for certain tumor markers. A biopsy may also be performed to confirm the diagnosis. \r\nTreatment for ovarian cancer may involve surgery to remove the ovaries, fallopian tubes, and uterus, as well as any nearby lymph nodes or other affected tissues. Chemotherapy may also be used to destroy cancer cells that remain after surgery. Targeted therapy and immunotherapy may also be used in some cases. \r\nEarly detection and treatment of ovarian cancer can improve outcomes and increase the chances of survival. Women with a family history of ovarian or breast cancer may be at increased risk and should discuss their risk and screening options with a doctor. ', NULL, '2023-05-23 08:19:23'),
(83, 2, 'Pancreatic Cancer ', 'Pancreatic cancer is a type of cancer that develops in the pancreas, which is a gland located in the abdomen that produces digestive enzymes and hormones that regulate blood sugar. Pancreatic cancer is a particularly aggressive type of cancer, and it often spreads rapidly to other parts of the body. \r\nThe exact cause of pancreatic cancer is not known, but certain risk factors may increase a person\'s likelihood of developing the disease. These risk factors may include a family history of pancreatic cancer, smoking, obesity, chronic pancreatitis, and certain genetic mutations. ', 'Abdominal pain \r\nBack pain \r\nUnexplained weight loss \r\nFatigue \r\nLoss of appetite \r\nJaundice (yellowing of the skin and eyes) \r\nChanges in bowel movements ', 'Diagnosis of pancreatic cancer may involve imaging tests such as CT scans, MRI, or ultrasound, as well as a biopsy to confirm the presence of cancerous cells. Blood tests may also be used to check for certain tumor markers. \r\nTreatment for pancreatic cancer may involve surgery to remove the tumor, as well as chemotherapy and radiation therapy to destroy any remaining cancer cells. In some cases, targeted therapy or immunotherapy may also be used. \r\nEarly detection and treatment of pancreatic cancer can improve outcomes and increase the chances of survival. However, because pancreatic cancer often does not cause symptoms until it has reached an advanced stage, it can be difficult to diagnose and treat. People with a family history of pancreatic cancer may be at increased risk and should discuss their risk and screening options with a doctor. ', NULL, '2023-05-23 08:20:55'),
(84, 2, 'Paralytic Shellfish Poisoning ', 'Paralytic Shellfish Poisoning (PSP) is a type of food poisoning that occurs after eating shellfish contaminated with a toxin produced by certain species of marine algae, such as dinoflagellates. These toxins can accumulate in the tissues of shellfish such as mussels, clams, oysters, and scallops, causing illness in humans and other animals that consume them. ', 'Tingling \r\nNumbness \r\nBurning sensations in the mouth, face, and limbs, followed by muscle weakness \r\nDifficulty breathing \r\nParalysis ', 'There is no known cure for PSP, and treatment mainly involves supportive care, such as respiratory assistance and fluids. In some cases, an antidote called atropine may be used to counteract the effects of the toxin. \r\nPrevention of PSP involves avoiding consumption of shellfish from areas known to be affected by harmful algal blooms. Health authorities may issue warnings or closures of shellfish harvesting areas if high levels of toxin are detected. \r\nPeople who eat shellfish, especially those who gather their own from the wild, should be aware of the risks of PSP and other types of shellfish poisoning, and should only consume shellfish that have been harvested from approved areas and have been properly cooked. ', NULL, '2023-05-23 08:21:32'),
(85, 2, 'Parkinson\'s Disease ', 'Parkinson\'s disease is a progressive neurodegenerative disorder that affects movement and can also affect cognition and mood. It is caused by the gradual loss of dopamine-producing cells in the brain, leading to a deficiency of dopamine, a neurotransmitter that plays a key role in movement control. ', 'Tremors \r\nRigidity \r\nStiffness \r\nSlowed movement \r\nDifficulty with balance coordination ', 'There is no cure for Parkinson\'s disease, but there are treatments available that can help manage symptoms. These treatments may include medications that help increase dopamine levels in the brain or that target other aspects of the disease, such as tremors or sleep problems. In some cases, surgery may be an option to help control symptoms. \r\nLifestyle modifications such as regular exercise and physical therapy can also be helpful in managing symptoms, as can occupational therapy to address issues with daily living activities. It is also important to have a good support system, including healthcare providers, family, and friends, who can help provide emotional support and assist with daily activities. \r\nAlthough Parkinson\'s disease is typically diagnosed in people over the age of 60, it can occur at any age. Researchers continue to study the disease and explore new treatments and therapies to improve outcomes for people living with Parkinson\'s disease. ', NULL, '2023-05-23 08:23:36'),
(86, 2, 'Pelvic Inflammatory Disease (PID) ', 'Pelvic inflammatory disease (PID) is an infection of the female reproductive organs, including the uterus, fallopian tubes, and ovaries. It is typically caused by bacteria that are sexually transmitted, such as Chlamydia trachomatis or Neisseria gonorrhoeae, but can also occur as a result of non-sexually transmitted infections. ', 'Pelvic pain \r\nAbdominal pain \r\nFever \r\nUnusual vaginal discharge \r\nPainful urination \r\nPainful sexual intercourse ', 'If left untreated, PID can lead to serious complications, such as chronic pelvic pain, infertility, ectopic pregnancy (a pregnancy outside of the uterus), and an increased risk of future infections. Treatment typically involves antibiotics to clear the infection, and in some cases hospitalization may be necessary. \r\nPrevention of PID involves practicing safe sex, using barrier methods such as condoms, and getting tested regularly for sexually transmitted infections. It is also important to seek prompt medical attention if you experience any symptoms of PID or other reproductive health concerns. ', NULL, '2023-05-23 08:24:20'),
(87, 2, 'Penile Cancer ', 'Penile cancer is a rare type of cancer that affects the tissue of the penis, usually developing in the skin or cells of the glands beneath the foreskin. The exact cause of penile cancer is not known, but it is believed to be associated with factors such as age, HPV infection, smoking, and poor hygiene. ', 'A lump or sore on the penis \r\nChanges in the skin color or texture of the penis \r\nDischarge or bleeding from the penis \r\nDifficulty urinating ', 'Treatment for penile cancer depends on the stage and location of the cancer, as well as the overall health of the patient. Surgery to remove the cancerous tissue may be the main treatment, and in some cases, radiation therapy and chemotherapy may be used in addition to or instead of surgery. \r\nPrevention of penile cancer involves practicing good hygiene, such as washing the penis regularly, and avoiding exposure to risk factors such as smoking and HPV infection. Safe sex practices, such as using condoms, can also reduce the risk of developing penile cancer. Early detection through regular self-examinations and routine medical checkups can also improve outcomes and increase the chances of successful treatment. ', NULL, '2023-05-23 08:25:00'),
(88, 2, 'Plague ', 'Plague is a serious bacterial infection caused by the bacterium Yersinia pestis. It is typically transmitted to humans through the bites of infected fleas that have bitten infected animals, such as rodents, squirrels, or prairie dogs. \r\nThere are three main types of plague: bubonic, septicemic, and pneumonic. Bubonic plague is the most common form and is characterized by swollen and painful lymph nodes, or \"buboes,\" as well as fever, chills, and fatigue. ', 'Fever \r\nChills \r\nRapid heartbeat \r\nAbdominal pain \r\nVomiting ', 'Plague is a serious and potentially life-threatening condition if left untreated. Treatment typically involves antibiotics, and in some cases hospitalization may be necessary. There is currently no vaccine available for plague. \r\nPrevention of plague involves avoiding contact with rodents, wearing protective clothing such as long pants and socks when in areas where rodents may be present, and using insect repellent to prevent flea bites. If you suspect that you may have been exposed to plague or are experiencing symptoms, seek medical attention immediately. ', NULL, '2023-05-23 10:04:08'),
(89, 2, 'Pneumococcal Disease ', 'Pneumococcal disease is an infection caused by the Streptococcus pneumoniae bacteria. It can lead to a variety of illnesses, including pneumonia, meningitis, and blood infections. The bacteria can be spread through respiratory droplets, such as when a person with the infection coughs or sneezes, or by direct contact with contaminated surfaces. ', 'Fever \r\nCough \r\nShortness of breath \r\nChest pain \r\nHeadache \r\nStiff neck \r\nConfusion \r\nSensitivity to light ', 'Vaccination is the most effective way to prevent pneumococcal disease. There are two types of pneumococcal vaccines: pneumococcal conjugate vaccine (PCV13) and pneumococcal polysaccharide vaccine (PPSV23). Both vaccines can help protect against pneumococcal disease, but they are recommended for different age groups and populations. \r\nTreatment for pneumococcal disease typically involves antibiotics, but in severe cases, hospitalization may be necessary. \r\nPrevention of pneumococcal disease also involves practicing good hygiene, such as washing hands regularly and covering the mouth and nose when coughing or sneezing. It is also important to avoid close contact with individuals who are sick with pneumococcal disease. ', NULL, '2023-05-23 10:04:57'),
(90, 2, 'Prostate Cancer ', 'Prostate cancer is a type of cancer that develops in the prostate gland, a small gland in the male reproductive system that produces seminal fluid. Prostate cancer is one of the most common types of cancer among men, and it usually develops in older men. ', 'Weak or interrupted urine flow \r\nFrequent urination \r\nDifficulty starting \r\nStopping urination \r\nPain or burning during urination \r\nBlood in the urine or semen \r\nErectile dysfunction \r\nPain in the lower back, hips, or thighs.', 'There are several tests used to screen for prostate cancer, including a prostate-specific antigen (PSA) blood test and a digital rectal exam. If these tests indicate the possibility of prostate cancer, further tests, such as a prostate biopsy, may be recommended. \r\nTreatment for prostate cancer depends on several factors, including the stage of the cancer, the patient\'s age and health, and the patient\'s personal preferences. Treatment options may include surgery, radiation therapy, chemotherapy, hormone therapy, or a combination of these treatments. \r\nPrevention of prostate cancer may involve maintaining a healthy lifestyle, such as eating a diet high in fruits and vegetables and low in red meat and fat, exercising regularly, and not smoking. Men should also discuss the benefits and risks of prostate cancer screening with their healthcare provider. ', NULL, '2023-05-23 10:06:56'),
(91, 2, 'Pubic Lice ', 'Pubic lice, also known as crabs, are tiny parasitic insects that live in the pubic hair of humans. They are spread through close physical contact, such as sexual contact, and can also be transmitted through shared clothing, towels, or bedding. ', 'Itching \r\n\r\nRedness, and irritation in the pubic area \r\nPresence of small, dark, oval-shaped insects or eggs in the pubic hair ', 'Pubic lice can be diagnosed by examining the affected area or by finding the eggs or insects in the pubic hair. Treatment involves using topical insecticide creams or lotions that kill the lice and their eggs. It is important to follow the instructions carefully and to apply the treatment to all affected areas, as well as any clothing, bedding, or towels that may have come into contact with the lice. \r\nTo prevent pubic lice, it is recommended to avoid close physical contact with infected individuals, to practice safe sex by using condoms, and to avoid sharing personal items such as clothing and towels. It is also important to maintain good personal hygiene by regularly washing the genital area and pubic hair. ', NULL, '2023-05-23 10:07:34'),
(92, 2, 'Zika Virus ', 'Zika virus is a viral infection that is primarily spread through the bite of infected Aedes mosquitoes. The virus can also be transmitted from a pregnant woman to her fetus during pregnancy, through sexual contact, and through blood transfusions. ', 'Fever \r\nRash \r\nJoint pain \r\nRed eyes ', 'There is no specific treatment for Zika virus, but supportive care can help to manage symptoms. Prevention measures include avoiding mosquito bites (such as using insect repellent, wearing long-sleeved shirts and pants, and staying indoors during peak mosquito activity), practicing safe sex, and avoiding travel to areas where Zika virus is endemic. \r\nPregnant women are particularly at risk of complications from Zika virus infection, and should take extra precautions to avoid exposure to the virus. If a pregnant woman has been exposed to Zika virus, she should be monitored closely by a healthcare provider. ', NULL, '2023-05-23 10:08:27'),
(93, 25, 'Rabies', 'Rabies is a viral infection that affects the nervous system and can be fatal if left untreated. It is typically spread through the bite or scratch of an infected animal, such as a dog, bat, or raccoon. ', 'Fever \r\nHeadache \r\nAnxiety\r\nConfusion\r\nHallucinations\r\nDifficulty swallowing\r\nSeizures', 'Treatment for rabies involves receiving a series of injections, including a vaccine and immune globulin, to prevent the virus from causing illness. It is important to seek medical attention immediately after being bitten by an animal, as treatment is most effective when given early. \r\n\r\n \r\n\r\nPrevention of rabies involves avoiding contact with wild or unfamiliar animals, vaccinating pets, and seeking prompt medical attention after any animal bite or scratch. In some cases, people who are at high risk of exposure to rabies, such as veterinarians or laboratory workers, may receive a pre-exposure vaccine to protect against the virus. ', NULL, '2023-05-23 10:14:33'),
(94, 25, 'Relapsing Fever ', 'Relapsing fever is a bacterial infection caused by certain species of Borrelia bacteria. It is typically transmitted through the bite of infected lice or ticks. ', 'Headache \r\nMuscle aches \r\nJoint pain \r\nChills \r\nNausea \r\nVomiting \r\nRash ', 'Diagnosis of relapsing fever involves testing blood samples for the presence of the bacteria. Treatment usually involves antibiotics, such as doxycycline or penicillin, which are effective in eliminating the infection. \r\n\r\n \r\n\r\nPrevention of relapsing fever involves avoiding exposure to infected lice and ticks. This may involve using insect repellent, wearing protective clothing, and regularly checking for ticks after spending time outdoors. It is also important to avoid close contact with people who have relapsing fever, as the infection can be spread through contact with their blood or bodily fluids. ', NULL, '2023-05-23 10:15:16'),
(95, 25, 'Ringworm', 'Ringworm is a common fungal infection of the skin that can affect different parts of the body, including the scalp, feet, groin, and nails. Despite its name, ringworm is not caused by a worm, but rather a type of fungus called dermatophytes. ', 'Ring-shaped rash on the skin\r\nRaised, red edges and clear skin in the middle\r\nItchy\r\nUncomfortable\r\nMay spread to other parts of the body or to other people through direct skin-to-skin contact', 'Treatment for ringworm typically involves applying antifungal creams, lotions, or powders to the affected area. In severe cases, oral antifungal medications may be necessary. It is also important to practice good hygiene, such as keeping the affected area clean and dry, avoiding sharing personal items, and washing bedding and clothing regularly to prevent the spread of infection. \r\n\r\n \r\n\r\nPrevention of ringworm involves maintaining good personal hygiene, avoiding contact with infected people or animals, and wearing protective clothing or footwear in environments where the fungus may be present, such as public showers or swimming pools. ', NULL, '2023-05-23 10:16:19'),
(96, 25, 'Rocky Mountain Spotted Fever ', 'Rocky Mountain spotted fever (RMSF) is a bacterial infection caused by the bacterium Rickettsia rickettsii. It is transmitted to humans through the bite of infected ticks, primarily the American dog tick, the Rocky Mountain wood tick, and the brown dog tick.', 'Fever \r\nHeadache \r\nMuscle aches \r\nNausea \r\nVomiting \r\nRash ', 'If left untreated, RMSF can lead to serious complications, such as kidney failure, heart failure, and brain damage. Treatment typically involves antibiotics, such as doxycycline, which is effective in eliminating the infection. \r\n\r\n \r\n\r\nPrevention of RMSF involves avoiding contact with infected ticks, wearing protective clothing when in tick-infested areas, using insect repellent, and regularly checking for ticks after spending time outdoors. It is also important to promptly remove any attached ticks using fine-tipped tweezers and to seek medical attention if you develop symptoms after a tick bite. ', NULL, '2023-05-23 10:17:17'),
(97, 25, 'Rotavirus ', 'Rotavirus is a highly contagious virus that causes gastroenteritis, which is inflammation of the stomach and intestines. It is a leading cause of severe diarrhea among infants and young children worldwide. \r\n\r\n \r\n\r\nThe virus spreads through contact with the feces of an infected person, and can be easily transmitted through contaminated food, water, or surfaces. ', 'Fever \r\nVomiting \r\nWatery diarrhea which can lead to dehydration if left untreated. ', 'Treatment for rotavirus infection focuses on relieving symptoms and preventing dehydration through the use of oral rehydration solutions. In severe cases, hospitalization may be necessary to provide intravenous fluids and electrolytes. \r\n\r\n \r\n\r\nPrevention of rotavirus infection primarily involves vaccination, which is recommended for all infants as part of their routine immunizations. It is also important to practice good hygiene, such as washing hands regularly and thoroughly, especially after using the bathroom, changing diapers, and before handling food. ', NULL, '2023-05-23 10:17:48'),
(98, 25, 'Salmonellosis ', 'Salmonellosis is an infection caused by the bacterium Salmonella. It is typically acquired by eating contaminated food, such as raw or undercooked poultry, eggs, or meat, or through contact with infected animals, feces, or contaminated water. ', 'Diarrhea \r\nFever \r\nAbdominal pain \r\nNausea ', 'Treatment for salmonellosis focuses on relieving symptoms and preventing dehydration through the use of oral rehydration solutions. Antibiotics may be necessary in severe cases or in patients at higher risk of complications, such as infants, elderly, or immunocompromised individuals. \r\n\r\n \r\n\r\nPrevention of salmonellosis involves proper food handling and preparation, such as thoroughly cooking meat and eggs, washing hands and surfaces frequently, and avoiding cross-contamination of food. It is also important to properly store and handle pet food and to avoid contact with reptiles, which are known carriers of Salmonella. ', NULL, '2023-05-23 10:18:20'),
(99, 25, 'Sarcoidosis ', 'Sarcoidosis is a disease in which tiny clusters of inflammatory cells called granulomas form in different parts of the body, most commonly in the lungs and lymph nodes. The cause of sarcoidosis is not fully understood, but it is believed to be a result of an abnormal immune response. ', 'Fatigue \r\nFever \r\nWeight loss \r\nShortness of breath \r\nChest pain \r\nSkin rashes \r\nJoint pain ', 'Diagnosis of sarcoidosis may involve a physical exam, imaging tests, and biopsy of the affected tissue. Treatment of sarcoidosis depends on the severity of the symptoms and the organs affected, but may involve the use of corticosteroids or other immunosuppressive drugs. \r\n\r\n \r\n\r\nSarcoidosis can affect people of any age, race, or gender, but it is more common in young adults and those of African or Scandinavian descent. The prognosis of sarcoidosis varies widely, and some patients may experience spontaneous remission while others may have chronic symptoms or progressive disease. ', NULL, '2023-05-23 10:18:58'),
(100, 25, 'Scabies ', 'Scabies is a contagious skin infestation caused by a mite called Sarcoptes scabiei. The mites burrow into the skin, causing intense itching and a rash. The infection is spread through direct skin-to-skin contact with an infected person, as well as through contaminated clothing, bedding, and furniture. ', 'Severe itching, especially at night \r\nA pimple-like rash \r\nPresence of visible burrows on the skin ', 'Diagnosis of scabies usually involves a physical exam and a skin scraping to confirm the presence of the mites. Treatment involves the use of topical medications, such as permethrin or ivermectin, which kill the mites and their eggs. It is also important to wash all clothing, bedding, and personal items in hot water and to vacuum or treat furniture and carpets to eliminate any remaining mites. \r\n\r\n \r\n\r\nScabies can affect people of all ages and is more common in crowded or unsanitary living conditions, such as nursing homes, prisons, and refugee camps. The infection can be prevented by avoiding close contact with infected individuals, practicing good hygiene, and avoiding sharing clothing or bedding with others. ', NULL, '2023-05-23 10:19:27'),
(101, 25, 'Scarlet fever ', 'Scarlet fever is a bacterial infection caused by group A Streptococcus bacteria. It mainly affects children between the ages of 5 and 15, but can also occur in adults. Scarlet fever is characterized by a bright red rash that covers most of the body, usually accompanied by a fever, sore throat, and swollen glands. ', 'Rash that typically starts on the chest and abdomen, then spreads to the rest of the body, including the arms, legs, and face. The rash may feel rough and sandpapery to the touch\r\nStrawberry-like appearance of the tongue and throat', 'Scarlet fever is spread through contact with an infected person or by touching objects contaminated with the bacteria, such as toys or utensils. The infection can be treated with antibiotics, such as penicillin, which help to reduce the duration and severity of symptoms, prevent complications, and reduce the spread of the infection. \r\n\r\n \r\n\r\nIf left untreated, scarlet fever can lead to more serious complications, such as kidney inflammation (nephritis), rheumatic fever, and heart damage. To prevent the spread of scarlet fever, it is important to practice good hygiene, such as washing hands frequently, covering coughs and sneezes, and avoiding close contact with infected individuals. ', NULL, '2023-05-23 10:20:33'),
(102, 25, 'Scombroid fish poisoning ', 'Scombroid fish poisoning is a type of food poisoning caused by the consumption of certain types of fish that have not been properly refrigerated or preserved. When fish such as tuna, mackerel, or mahi-mahi are not stored at the proper temperature after being caught, bacteria on the fish can multiply and produce high levels of histamine, which can cause symptoms of poisoning when consumed. ', 'Flushing \r\nHeadache \r\nSweating \r\nPalpitations \r\nAbdominal cramps \r\nNausea \r\nVomiting \r\nDiarrhea ', 'Scombroid fish poisoning can be diagnosed through a combination of symptoms and a history of fish consumption. Treatment usually involves supportive care, such as antihistamines for the symptoms and fluids to prevent dehydration. In severe cases, hospitalization may be necessary. \r\n\r\n \r\n\r\nTo prevent scombroid fish poisoning, it is important to ensure that fish are stored at the proper temperature, either by refrigeration or freezing, and that they are properly preserved if being transported. It is also important to cook fish thoroughly to kill any bacteria that may be present. ', NULL, '2023-05-23 10:21:05'),
(103, 25, 'Seoul Virus ', ' Seoul virus is a type of hantavirus that can cause a mild to moderate illness in humans known as Seoul virus infection or Seoul hantavirus disease. The virus is carried by rodents, particularly the brown rat, and can be transmitted to humans through contact with rodent urine, feces, saliva, or nesting materials, or through bites from infected rodents. ', 'Fever \r\nHeadache \r\nMuscle aches \r\nChills \r\nNausea ', 'Seoul virus infection can be diagnosed through blood tests that detect antibodies to the virus. Treatment typically involves supportive care, such as rest and fluids, to manage the symptoms. In some cases, antiviral medications may be prescribed. \r\n\r\n \r\n\r\nPreventing Seoul virus infection involves taking measures to avoid contact with rodents, such as sealing up holes and gaps in buildings, removing potential rodent food sources, and using protective measures when handling rodents or their materials. It is also important to practice good hygiene, such as washing hands thoroughly after handling rodents or their materials. ', NULL, '2023-05-23 10:22:06'),
(104, 25, 'Severe acute respiratory syndrome (SARS) ', 'Severe acute respiratory syndrome (SARS) is a viral respiratory illness that first emerged in Southern China in 2002. The illness is caused by a coronavirus, known as the SARS coronavirus, or SARS-CoV. \r\n\r\n \r\n\r\nSARS is highly contagious and can spread through close person-to-person contact or by coming into contact with contaminated surfaces or objects. The virus is primarily transmitted through respiratory droplets produced when an infected person coughs or sneezes. ', 'Fever \r\nHeadache \r\nBody aches \r\n Cough \r\nShortness of breate \r\nDifficulty breathing ', 'There is no specific treatment for SARS, and management involves supportive care, such as oxygen therapy, mechanical ventilation, and antiviral medications. Prevention measures include practicing good hygiene, such as washing hands frequently, avoiding close contact with infected individuals, and wearing personal protective equipment, such as masks and gloves, when caring for infected patients. \r\n\r\n \r\n\r\nAfter a large outbreak in 2002-2003, SARS was successfully contained, and no cases have been reported since 2004. However, the emergence of COVID-19, another coronavirus-related illness, has highlighted the ongoing threat posed by these viruses and the importance of preparedness and surveillance to prevent future outbreaks. ', NULL, '2023-05-23 10:22:49'),
(105, 25, 'Sexually Transmitted Diseases (STD) ', 'Sexually transmitted diseases (STDs), also known as sexually transmitted infections (STIs), are infections that are spread through sexual contact, including vaginal, anal, and oral sex. They can be caused by bacteria, viruses, parasites, and other microorganisms. \r\n\r\n \r\n\r\nSTDs can have serious health consequences, including infertility, chronic pain, and an increased risk of certain types of cancer. Some STDs can also be passed from a pregnant woman to her baby during childbirth. ', 'Chlamydia\r\nGonorrhea\r\nSyphilis\r\nHuman papillomavirus (HPV)\r\nGenital herpes\r\nHIV/AIDS.\r\nMany people who have STDs may not experience any symptoms, but they can still spread the infection to others. ', 'Treatment of STDs depends on the specific infection and may include antibiotics, antiviral medications, or other types of medication. It\'s important to seek treatment if you suspect you may have an STD or have been exposed to someone with an STD to prevent complications and further transmission. ', NULL, '2023-05-23 10:23:54'),
(106, 25, 'Shigellosis ', 'Shigellosis, also known as bacillary dysentery, is an infectious disease caused by bacteria of the genus Shigella. The disease is spread by consuming contaminated food or water, or through direct contact with an infected person. ', 'Diarrhea (which may contain blood or mucus) \r\nFever \r\nAbdominal pain ', 'Treatment for shigellosis typically involves rest, hydration, and antibiotics to help speed recovery and prevent complications. In some cases, hospitalization may be necessary for severe cases or for people who are at high risk of complications. ', NULL, '2023-05-23 10:24:19'),
(107, 25, 'Skin Cancer ', 'Skin cancer is a type of cancer that develops in the cells of the skin. It is often caused by exposure to ultraviolet (UV) radiation from the sun or tanning beds. There are several types of skin cancer, including: \r\n\r\n \r\n\r\nBasal cell carcinoma: This is the most common type of skin cancer. It usually appears as a small, shiny bump or a red, scaly patch that grows slowly and rarely spreads to other parts of the body. \r\n\r\n \r\n\r\nSquamous cell carcinoma: This type of skin cancer typically appears as a firm, red bump or a scaly, crusted patch on the skin. It can spread to other parts of the body if left untreated. \r\n\r\n \r\n\r\nMelanoma: This is the most serious type of skin cancer. It can appear as a new mole or an existing mole that changes in size, shape, or color. Melanoma can spread quickly to other parts of the body and can be life-threatening if not treated early. ', 'Pearly or translucent bump or spot\r\nScar-like lesion\r\nNon-healing sore or crusty spot\r\nFirm, red nodule\r\nScaly or crusted flat lesion\r\nPersistent sore or ulcer\r\nNew or changing mole\r\nAsymmetrical or irregularly bordered moles\r\nMoles with varied colors, larger size, or unusual sensations (itching, bleeding, pain)', 'Treatment for skin cancer depends on the type and stage of the cancer. Surgery is often used to remove the cancerous cells, while radiation therapy and chemotherapy may be used in more advanced cases. Preventive measures such as avoiding excessive sun exposure, using sunscreen, and wearing protective clothing can help reduce the risk of developing skin cancer. ', NULL, '2023-05-23 10:26:05'),
(108, 25, 'Smallpox ', 'Smallpox is a contagious and potentially fatal viral disease caused by the variola virus. It is characterized by a high fever and a rash that covers the entire body with raised bumps that fill with fluid and then scab over. Smallpox is highly infectious, and spreads through contact with infected individuals or contaminated objects. \r\n\r\n \r\n\r\nSmallpox was a major global health threat for centuries, causing outbreaks and epidemics that killed millions of people. However, thanks to a worldwide vaccination campaign, smallpox was eradicated in 1980, and it is the only human disease to have been completely eradicated. Today, the variola virus is known to exist only in laboratory stocks, and the World Health Organization recommends that all known stocks be destroyed to prevent accidental or intentional release of the virus. ', 'High Fever\r\nMalaise\r\nSevere Headache\r\nBackache\r\nVomiting', 'The smallpox vaccine is no longer routinely administered, as the disease has been eradicated, but samples of the virus are kept in high-security laboratories for research purposes, and in the event of a bioterrorism attack. ', NULL, '2023-05-23 10:28:18'),
(109, 25, 'Stomach Cancer ', 'Stomach cancer, also known as gastric cancer, is a type of cancer that starts in the cells lining the stomach. The exact cause of stomach cancer is not well understood, but certain factors have been linked to an increased risk, including a diet high in smoked, pickled, or salted foods, a history of stomach surgery, chronic inflammation of the stomach lining, and infection with Helicobacter pylori bacteria. ', 'Indigestion \r\nHeartburn \r\nAbdominal pain \r\nNausea \r\nVomiting \r\nLoss of appetite \r\nUnexplained weight loss \r\nBlack or bloody stools ', 'Treatment for stomach cancer depends on the stage of the cancer and other factors, but may include surgery to remove the cancerous tissue, chemotherapy, radiation therapy, or a combination of these approaches. In some cases, treatment may also include targeted therapies or immunotherapy. \r\n\r\n \r\n\r\nPrevention of stomach cancer can be challenging, but some strategies that may help reduce the risk include eating a healthy diet rich in fruits and vegetables, avoiding tobacco and excessive alcohol consumption, treating H. pylori infection if present, and managing conditions that may increase the risk of stomach cancer, such as chronic gastritis. ', NULL, '2023-05-23 10:28:52'),
(110, 25, 'Tetanus ', 'Tetanus, also known as lockjaw, is a serious bacterial infection caused by the Clostridium tetani bacterium. The bacteria produces a toxin that affects the nervous system and causes muscle stiffness and spasms, particularly in the jaw and neck. Tetanus is usually contracted through a cut or wound contaminated with the bacteria. ', 'Difficulty breathing and swallowing \r\nSeizures \r\nDeath ', 'Tetanus can be prevented through vaccination and prompt treatment with tetanus antitoxin if an individual is exposed to the bacteria. ', NULL, '2023-05-23 10:29:10'),
(111, 25, 'Testicular cancer ', 'Testicular cancer is a type of cancer that develops in the testicles, which are the male reproductive glands located in the scrotum. It is a relatively rare form of cancer, accounting for only about 1% of all male cancers. The cause of testicular cancer is not fully understood, but certain risk factors, such as a family history of the disease, undescended testicles, and abnormal testicular development, may increase the risk of developing the cancer. ', 'A lump or swelling in the testicles \r\nPain or discomfort in the testicles or scrotum \r\nFeeling of heaviness in the scrotum ', 'Treatment for testicular cancer typically involves surgery to remove the affected testicle, followed by radiation therapy, chemotherapy, or a combination of both, depending on the stage and severity of the cancer. ', NULL, '2023-05-23 10:29:29');
