(112, 25, 'Thyroid cancer ', 'Thyroid cancer is a type of cancer that develops in the cells of the thyroid gland, which is located in the neck and produces hormones that regulate metabolism. The cause of thyroid cancer is not fully understood, but certain risk factors, such as exposure to radiation, a family history of the disease, and certain inherited genetic mutations, may increase the risk of developing the cancer. ', 'A lump or swelling in the neck \r\nDifficulty swallowing \r\nHoarseness or other changes in the voice \r\nPersistent coughing ', 'Treatment for thyroid cancer typically involves surgery to remove the affected part of the thyroid gland, followed by radioactive iodine therapy or other types of radiation therapy, depending on the stage and severity of the cancer. In some cases, chemotherapy may also be used to treat thyroid cancer. ', NULL, '2023-05-23 10:29:53'),
(113, 25, 'Tuberculosis (TB) ', 'Tuberculosis (TB) is a bacterial infection caused by a bacterium called Mycobacterium tuberculosis. It primarily affects the lungs but can also affect other parts of the body such as the brain, spine, or kidneys. TB is spread through the air when an infected person coughs, sneezes, or speaks. ', 'Persistent cough \r\nFever \r\nNight sweats \r\nWeight loss ', 'While TB can be treated with antibiotics, drug-resistant strains of the bacteria have emerged, making the disease more difficult to treat. TB remains a significant global health problem, particularly in developing countries with poor healthcare infrastructure. ', NULL, '2023-05-23 10:30:13'),
(114, 25, 'Typhoid fever ', 'Typhoid fever is a bacterial infection caused by the bacterium Salmonella Typhi. It spreads through contaminated food and water or close contact with an infected person. ', 'High fever \r\nWeakness \r\nStomach pain \r\nHeadache \r\nLoss of appetite \r\nDiarrhea \r\nConstipation ', 'Without treatment, typhoid fever can lead to complications such as intestinal bleeding or perforation, and can be fatal in some cases. Treatment typically involves antibiotics, and prevention involves vaccination and practicing good hygiene and sanitation measures. ', NULL, '2023-05-23 10:30:31'),
(115, 25, 'Vaginitis', 'Vaginitis is an inflammation or infection of the vagina, which is the muscular canal that extends from the external genitalia to the cervix in women. Vaginitis can be caused by a variety of factors, including bacteria, yeast, viruses, and irritants. \r\n\r\n \r\n\r\nBacterial vaginosis, yeast infections, and trichomoniasis are the most common types of vaginitis. Bacterial vaginosis is caused by an overgrowth of bacteria in the vagina, while yeast infections are caused by an overgrowth of the fungus Candida. Trichomoniasis is a sexually transmitted infection caused by the parasite Trichomonas vaginalis. ', 'Itching \r\nBurning \r\nInflammation of the vaginal tissues \r\nAbnormal vaginal discharge \r\nPain or discomfort during sexual intercourse or urination ', 'Treatment for vaginitis typically involves addressing the underlying cause of the infection or inflammation. This may involve antibiotics, antifungal medications, or antiparasitic medications, depending on the specific type of infection. In addition, practicing good hygiene and avoiding irritants can help to prevent the development of vaginitis. \r\n\r\n \r\n\r\nIt is important to see a healthcare provider if you are experiencing symptoms of vaginitis, as some infections can have serious complications if left untreated. ', NULL, '2023-05-23 10:30:55'),
(116, 25, 'Viral Gastroenteritis and Norovirus ', 'Viral gastroenteritis, also known as the stomach flu, is an inflammation of the stomach and intestines caused by a viral infection. The most common viruses that cause viral gastroenteritis are the norovirus and rotavirus, although other viruses can also cause the condition. \r\n\r\n \r\n\r\nViral gastroenteritis is highly contagious and can spread through contact with contaminated surfaces, food, or water, as well as through close contact with an infected person. The virus can survive on surfaces for several days, so it is important to practice good hygiene to prevent the spread of the infection. ', 'Diarrhea\r\nNausea\r\nVomiting\r\nAbdominal cramps\r\nFever\r\nHeadaches', 'Treatment for viral gastroenteritis typically involves supportive care, such as rest, hydration, and symptom relief. In severe cases, hospitalization may be necessary to receive intravenous fluids and electrolytes. Antibiotics are not effective against viral infections and are not recommended for the treatment of viral gastroenteritis. \r\n\r\nPrevention measures include washing hands frequently with soap and water, avoiding contact with people who are sick, avoiding sharing personal items such as towels or utensils, and ensuring that food and water are properly prepared and stored to prevent contamination. Vaccines are available to prevent rotavirus infections, which are a common cause of viral gastroenteritis in young children. ', NULL, '2023-05-23 10:31:56'),
(117, 25, 'West Nile Virus ', 'West Nile virus (WNV) is a mosquito-borne virus that can cause illness in humans and animals. It is a member of the Flaviviridae family of viruses, which also includes the viruses that cause dengue fever and yellow fever. \r\n\r\nThe virus is primarily transmitted through the bite of infected mosquitoes. ', 'Fever \r\nHeadache \r\nBody aches \r\nJoint pain \r\nVomiting \r\nDiarrhea \r\nRash ', 'There is no specific treatment for WNV, and most people who contract the virus recover on their own. Supportive care, such as rest, fluids, and over-the-counter pain relievers, can help to alleviate symptoms. People who develop severe symptoms may require hospitalization for supportive care. \r\n\r\n \r\n\r\nPrevention measures for WNV include reducing exposure to mosquitoes by using insect repellent, wearing long-sleeved shirts and pants, and staying indoors during peak mosquito activity. Mosquito breeding sites, such as standing water, should be eliminated whenever possible to reduce the number of mosquitoes in an area. There is also a vaccine available for horses to prevent WNV infection ', NULL, '2023-05-23 10:32:26'),
(118, 25, 'Whooping cough (Pertussis) ', 'Whooping cough, also known as pertussis, is a highly contagious respiratory infection caused by the bacterium Bordetella pertussis. The infection is characterized by severe coughing spells that can last for several weeks or months, often causing a \"whooping\" sound as the person gasps for air after coughing. \n\nWhooping cough is spread through respiratory droplets when an infected person coughs or sneezes. ', 'Runny nose\nSneezing\nMild cough\nVomiting\nExhaustion\nDifficulty breathing', 'It can be prevented with a vaccine, but outbreaks can occur when vaccination rates are low. Treatment for whooping cough usually involves antibiotics to control the infection and supportive care, such as rest and hydration, to manage symptoms.\n\nPrevention measures include vaccination, frequent hand washing, covering the mouth and nose when coughing or sneezing, and staying home from work or school when sick. Vaccination is particularly important for pregnant women, as the vaccine can protect newborns from the infection during the first few months of life, when they are most vulnerable to severe complications from whooping cough.', NULL, '2023-05-23 10:35:06'),
(119, 25, 'Yellow Fever ', 'Yellow fever is a viral disease that is transmitted by infected mosquitoes. The disease is caused by the yellow fever virus, which belongs to the Flaviviridae family of viruses. Yellow fever is primarily found in tropical and subtropical regions of Africa and South America. ', 'Fever \r\nHeadache \r\nMuscle pain \r\nNausea \r\nVomiting \r\nFatigue', 'There is no specific treatment for yellow fever, but supportive care can help to manage symptoms and prevent complications. Prevention measures include vaccination, mosquito control measures (such as eliminating standing water and using insect repellent), and taking precautions to avoid mosquito bites (such as wearing long-sleeved shirts and pants and staying indoors during peak mosquito activity). \r\n\r\n \r\n\r\nYellow fever is a potentially deadly disease, and vaccination is highly recommended for people who live in or travel to areas where the disease is endemic. Some countries require proof of yellow fever vaccination before allowing entry, so it is important to check the vaccination requirements before traveling to these areas. ', NULL, '2023-05-23 10:33:23');
